    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "Available is a 2008 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8 engine. This power plant utilizes eight individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio to produce 414 hp at a 8,400 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M Differential Lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution across the rear axle. The chassis remains sharp, benefitting from the M-specific aluminum subframe and Electronic Damping Control (EDC). Recent service highlights include a proactive replacement of the rod bearings and throttle actuators, addressing the primary mechanical concerns of the S65 platform. While the exterior displays minor road patina, the mechanical synchronization and throttle response are precise, offering a visceral, analog performance profile for the dedicated enthusiast.",
